250 g Ground Beef
0.17 cup Panko Breadcrumbs
1 unit Mango
170 g Coleslaw Cabbage Mix
1 unit Mini Cucumber
1 unit Lime
28 g Peanuts, chopped
2 tbsp Sweet Chili Sauce
1 tbsp Seasoned Rice Vinegar
7 g Thai Spice Blend
2 tbsp Milk*
¼ tsp Sugar*
1 tbsp Oil*
0.38 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, lightly oil the grill.
While you prep, preheat the grill to medium-high (approx. 500°F).
Wash and dry all produce.
Peel, pit, then cut mango into 1/4-inch matchsticks.
Halve cucumber lengthwise, then cut into 1/2-inch half-moons. Season with salt.
Zest, then juice half the lime. Reserve remaining lime for grilling in step 4.

To a medium bowl, add beef, Thai Spice Blend, half the panko (use all for 4 servings), 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) milk and 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) salt. Season with pepper, then combine.
Form beef mixture into 6 (12) 2-inch-wide patties, then place on a plate.
Gather koftas, remaining lime, a clean plate, a piece of foil and any cooking tools, then head out to the grill!

To one side of the grill, add koftas. Close lid and grill for 3-5 min per side, flipping once, until cooked through.**
Transfer to the clean plate, then cover with foil to keep warm.

Meanwhile, add lime to the other side of the grill. Grill for 1-3 min, until grill marks form.

In a large bowl, whisk together vinegar, 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) lime zest, 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) lime juice, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil and 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) sugar. Season with salt and pepper.
Add coleslaw cabbage mix, cucumbers and mangoes, then toss to coat.

When the grilled lime has slightly cooled, cut into wedges.
Divide koftas and mango slaw between plates.
Drizzle sweet chili sauce over koftas.
Sprinkle peanuts over top.
Squeeze a grilled lime wedge over top, if you like.